title: "Actual Proof": Herbie Hancock, Wayne Shorter & Terence Blanchard on COVID, BLM, and Wayne's legacy

fulltitle: "Actual Proof": Herbie Hancock, Wayne Shorter & Terence Blanchard on COVID, BLM, and Wayne's legacy
description:
Please consider donating to the Wayne Shorter Fund, for Wayne's ongoing medical needs: https://www.sfjazz.org/waynetipjar"

This incredible video is a true gathering of jazz titans, bringing together the legendary Herbie Hancock, trumpet giant and master composer Terence Blanchard, and SFJAZZ Fridays at Five tribute artist Wayne Shorter for a Zoom hangout. They discuss Wayne’s iconic music, the Black Lives Matter movement during this turbulent time, our new shared reality under the coronavirus pandemic, and how Herbie and Wayne’s music has remained enduringly relevant, always speaking to the times with grace and poignancy. Finally, the three talk about the second SFJAZZ Fridays At Five Celebration of Wayne Shorter, which featured performances from Herbie, Terence, Terrace Martin, and Wayne’s Quartet members Danilo Pérez, John Patitucci, and Brian Blade.
